{"title_page": "K R Balakrishnan", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical person\n| name              = K R Balakrishnan\n| image             =\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_name        = <!-- only use if different from name above -->\n| birth_date        = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> \n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)  -->\n| death_place       = \n| death_cause       = \n| nationality       = Indian\n| citizenship       = \n| education         = [[MBBS]], [[M.S.]], M.Ch.\n| occupation        = \n| years_active      = 1982 to Present\n| known_for         = [[Heart Transplantation]], [[Paediatric]] [[Cardiac Surgery]], [[Congestive Heart Failure]], [[Lung transplants]]\n| relations         = \n| website           = \n| profession        = [[Cardiothoracic]] & [[transplant surgeon]]\n| field             = \n| work_institutions = MGM Healthcare, Chennai\n| specialism        = \n| research_field    = \n| notable_works     = \n| prizes            =  \n*FICCI  Special Jury Award, 2017\n*Best Doctor Award by the Tamilnadu Government, 2017\n*Double Helical National Health Award, 2017\n| child             = \n| module2           = \n| signature         = \n}}\n\n'''K R Balakrishnan''' is an Indian [[cardiothoracic]], senior heart transplant surgeon and currently the Chairman of Cardiac Sciences, and the Director of Institute of Heart and Lung Transplant and Mechanical Circulatory Support at MGM Healthcare Chennai<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mgmhealthcare.in/|title=Healthcare {{!}} Best Super-MultiSpecialty Hospital in Chennai|website=MGM|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-13}}</ref>. He was the director of cardiac sciences at [[Fortis Malar Hospital]] Chennai till October 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Remembering India\u2019s first heart transplant surgery |url=https://www.livemint.com/Science/ER42epr7fhSfpB06bpgYPI/Remembering-Indias-first-heart-transplant-surgery.html |work=livemint |date=3 August 2016 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Three years after heart transplant, HR executive to run Mumbai marathon - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/three-years-after-heart-transplant-hr-exec-to-run-mumbai-marathon/articleshow/67463236.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kirpal |first1=Viney |title=Hearts are for giving |url=https://www.thehindu.com/opinion/open-page/hearts-are-for-giving/article26686700.ece |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=31 March 2019}}</ref> Balakrishnan performed the first permanent artificial heart transplant in India with HeartMate II LVAD and performed the largest number of heart transplants in India. He has performed over 16000 cardiac surgeries for various types of heart diseases and disorders till date. He has performed several first cardiac surgeries in India that includes the first pediatric heart transplant on a 2 year old Russian kid. He also did the first LVAD and HVAD pump transplant in India in 2012 and 2013 respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian boy, 8, embraces \u2018rejected\u2019 heart at Chennai hospital - Times of India \u25ba |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/russian-boy-8-embraces-rejected-heart-at-chennai-hospital/articleshow/63375518.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\nHe is the member of [[Indian Medical Association]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018VNIT being noticed at national stage due to Kutuhal\u2019 - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/vnit-being-noticed-at-national-stage-due-to-kutuhal/articleshow/67933725.cms |website=The Times of India}}</ref>\nFortis hospital has performed 100 free heart surgeries of needy children in India under the supervision of Balakrishnan funded by some clubs and Aishwarya Trust.<ref>{{cite web |title=Aishwarya Trust funds 55 successful Heart Transplants |url=https://www.apnnews.com/aishwarya-trust-funds-55-successful-heart-transplants/ |publisher=APN News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ramakrishnan |first1=Deepa H. |title=100 free heart surgeries and a million smiles |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/100-free-heart-surgeries-and-a-million-smiles/article24531777.ece |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=27 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bengaluru: Heart transplant saves 13-yr-old boy |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/050918/bengaluru-heart-transplant-saves-13-yr-old-boy.html |website=Deccan Chronicle |language=en |date=5 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nK R Balakrishnan earned MBBS degree from [[JIPMER]], Pondicherry in the year 1976. He completed [[Master of Surgery|MS]] in General Surgery from [[AIIMS]], New Delhi in 1980. Balakrishnan also qualified [[M.Ch.]] in Cardio Thoracic Surgery from [[KEM Hospital]], Mumbai, in the year 1982.\n\nBalakrishnan was the Professor and Head of Cardio Thoracic and Vascular Surgery at [[Sri Ramachandra Medical College and Research Institute]], Chennai from 1994 to 2008.<ref>{{cite news |title=INTERVIEW: Dr. K R Balakrishnan, Director, Cardiac Sciences, Fortis Malar Hospital, Chennai - ET HealthWorld |url=https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/interview-dr-k-r-balakrishnan-director-cardiac-sciences-fortis-malar-hospital-chennai/49853763 |work=ETHealthworld.com |language=en}}</ref>\n\nBalakrishnan has successfully done 200 heart transplant surgeries till 2012.<ref>{{cite web |title=Missing links |url=https://www.theweek.in/health/cover/2018/06/16/missing-links.html |website=The Week |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09e8\u09e6\u09e6 \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0\u09b0 \u09b9\u09c3\u09a6\u09af\u09bc \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09be\u09aa\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09b2\u09c7\u09a8 \u09a4\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf |url=https://eisamay.indiatimes.com/nation/dr-k-r-balakrishnan-at-fortis-is-well-experienced-cardiothoracic-surgery-doctor/articleshow/64267022.cms |work=Eisamay |date=22 May 2018 |language=bn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chennai: High risk lung transplant done |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/220818/chennai-high-risk-lung-transplant-done.html |website=Deccan Chronicle |language=en |date=22 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Nag |first1=Jayatri NagJayatri |last2=May 21 |first2=Bangalore Mirror Bureau |title=Bengaluru man\u2019s heart flown to Kolkata, cops create green corridor for transplant|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/bangalore/others/bengaluru-mans-heart-flown-to-kolkata-cops-create-green-corridor-for-transplant/articleshow/64261209.cms |work=Bangalore Mirror |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Strong-Willed Man Who Underwent Heart Transplant Three Years Ago Is Now Running Marathons |url=https://www.indiatimes.com/news/india/strong-willed-man-who-underwent-heart-transplant-three-years-ago-is-now-running-marathons-360206.html |website=indiatimes.com |language=en |date=11 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe has successfully performed bypass surgery of a shop owner from Gujarat \"Jaisukhabi Thakur\" who had no pulse rate.<ref>{{cite news |title=45 minutes after heart stops, man revived, gets new heart |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/45-minutes-after-heart-stops-man-revived-gets-new-heart/article8496269.ece |work=The Hindu |date=20 April 2016 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Doctors in Chennai hospital revive patient's heart 45 minutes after it stops beating - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Doctors-in-Chennai-hospital-revive-patients-heart-45-minutes-after-it-stops-beating/articleshow/51895298.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\nDr Balakrishnan has played a pioneering role in starting the Center for Heart Failure Management in Fortis Malar Hospital, Chennai which is the very first center in the country for Comprehensive Cardiac care. He is associated with academics and has over 30 publications to his name in renowned national and international medical journals.\n\n==Experience==\n*1.Senior Registrar to Sir Brian Baratt-Boyes, Cardio-Thoracic Unit, Green Lane Hospital, Auckland, New Zealand 1987-1988\n*2.Fellow in Cardiac Surgery, Oregon Health Sciences, University and St. Vincent Hospital Portland, OREGON with Dr.Albert Starr 1989-90\n*3.Specialist Cardiac Surgeon, Railway Hospital, Perambur, Madras JUNE 1990 to AUGUST 199\n\n==Awards & recognitions==\n*FICCI Special Jury Award 2017<ref>{{cite web |title=FICCI awards Dr KR Balakrishnan for his contribution to Healthcare,Medical Dialogues,Aug 31, 2017 |url=http://www.ficci.in/ficci-in-news-page.asp?nid=13112 |website=ficci.in}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Dr K R Balakrishnan awarded FICCI Special Jury Award for Contributions to Healthcare |url=https://thisweekindia.news/article/dr-k-r-balakrishnan-awarded-ficci-special-jury-award-for-contributions-to-healthcare/9778 |website=This Week India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Dr K R Balakrishnan awarded FICCI Special Jury Award for Contributions to Healthcare and Medical Science |url=http://cdn.fortishealthcare.com/0.81673000_1504010999_dr-kr-balakrishnan-awarded-ficci-special-jury-award.pdf |website=fortishealthcare.com}}</ref>\n*Best Doctor Award by the Tamilnadu Government in 2017<ref>{{cite web |title=Tamil Nadu Government honours Dr KR Balakrishnan with Best Medical Practitioner\u2019s Award, 2017 {{!}} ChennaiCityNews |url=http://www.chennaicitynews.net/news/tamil-nadu-government-honours-dr-kr-balakrishnan-with-best-medical-practitioners-award-2017-50658/ |publisher=Chennaicity News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tamil Nadu govt honours doctor who attested Jayalalithaa\u2019s thumb impression - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/tamil-nadu-govt-honours-doctor-who-attested-jayalalithaas-thumb-impression/articleshow/59357397.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n*Double Helical National Health Award in 2017<ref>{{cite web |title=Dr Balakrishnan of Fortis awarded for his contributions to healthcare |url=https://ehealth.eletsonline.com/2017/09/dr-balakrishnan-of-fortis-awarded-for-his-contributions-to-healthcare-research/ |publisher=eletsonline.com}}</ref>\n*Patent for Low Cost Ventricular Assist Device{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n*Patent for Flexible Polyurethane Membrane{{citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n==Research Interests==\n*1.Causative mechanisms of diffuse coronary artery disease, study using coronary endarterectomy specimens and electron microscopy and immunohistochemistry\n*2.Cellular and molecular mechanisms in ventricular hypertrophy, especially in Tetralogy of Fallot\n*3.Biomechanical stresses in atherosclerotic plaques and effect of calcification on plaque vulnerability\n*4.Finite element modeling of the human heart, including aortic and mitral valve\n*5.Fetal cardiomyocyte culture using 3D collagen scaffolds ( Dept. of Biotechnology funding)\n*6. Multiaxial testing of cardiac soft tissues and 3D modeling ( Dept. of biotechnology funding )\n*7. Rapid 3 D prototype of congenital heart disease\n*8.prototype development of an implantable, intracardiac pump\n*9. A prototype for the percutaneous mitral valve.\n\n==Satelite Centers Established==\n*1.Krishna Heart center, Cuddalore, Tamil Nadu. We have done over 250 Coronary bypass procedures in this rural set up with no mortality and over 5000 cath lab procedures in this center serving a rural populace.\n*2. Pondicherry Heart foundation: Established last year, we are doing around 3-5 heart operations a week and the work is likely to increase with time as more staff are recruited.\n*3.Tirupur Heart Institute: Open heart program started recently.\n*4. Ongoing surgical programs started with our expertise in Nairobi, Kenya, and Dhaka, Bangladesh.\n\n==Research Publications==\nhttps://www.researchgate.net/profile/Komarakshi_Balakrishnan\n\n==Resources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uPv_MVHvjoY   Interview with Economic Times Healthworld]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CvI_qd2belA   Dr K R Balakrishnan Interview with HYBIZTV]\n*[https://www.fortismalar.com/doctor/dr-kr-balakrishnan-leading-heart-transplant-surgeon-chennai-india   Dr K R Balakrishnan Biography]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balakrishnan, K R}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian cardiac surgeons]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n{{cat improve|date=August 2019}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical person\n| name              = K R Balakrishnan\n| image             =\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_name        = <!-- only use if different from name above -->\n| birth_date        = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> \n| birth_place       = \n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)  -->\n| death_place       = \n| death_cause       = \n| nationality       = Indian\n| citizenship       = \n| education         = [[MBBS]], [[M.S.]], M.Ch.\n| occupation        = \n| years_active      = 1982 to Present\n| known_for         = [[Heart Transplantation]], [[Paediatric]] [[Cardiac Surgery]], [[Congestive Heart Failure]], [[Lung transplants]]\n| relations         = \n| website           = \n| profession        = [[Cardiothoracic]] & [[transplant surgeon]]\n| field             = \n| work_institutions = MGM Healthcare, Chennai\n| specialism        = \n| research_field    = \n| notable_works     = \n| prizes            =  \n*FICCI  Special Jury Award, 2017\n*Best Doctor Award by the Tamilnadu Government, 2017\n*Double Helical National Health Award, 2017\n| child             = \n| module2           = \n| signature         = \n}}\n\n'''K R Balakrishnan''' is an Indian [[cardiothoracic]], senior heart transplant surgeon and currently the Chairman of Cardiac Sciences, and the Director of Institute of Heart and Lung Transplant and Mechanical Circulatory Support at MGM Healthcare Chennai<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mgmhealthcare.in/|title=Healthcare {{!}} Best Super-MultiSpecialty Hospital in Chennai|website=MGM|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-13}}</ref>. He was the director of cardiac sciences at [[Fortis Malar Hospital]] Chennai till October 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Remembering India\u2019s first heart transplant surgery |url=https://www.livemint.com/Science/ER42epr7fhSfpB06bpgYPI/Remembering-Indias-first-heart-transplant-surgery.html |work=livemint |date=3 August 2016 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Three years after heart transplant, HR executive to run Mumbai marathon - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/three-years-after-heart-transplant-hr-exec-to-run-mumbai-marathon/articleshow/67463236.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kirpal |first1=Viney |title=Hearts are for giving |url=https://www.thehindu.com/opinion/open-page/hearts-are-for-giving/article26686700.ece |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |date=31 March 2019}}</ref> Balakrishnan performed the first permanent artificial heart transplant in India with HeartMate II LVAD and performed the largest number of heart transplants in India. He has performed over 16000 cardiac surgeries for various types of heart diseases and disorders till date. He has performed several first cardiac surgeries in India that includes the first pediatric heart transplant on a 2 year old Russian kid. He also did the first LVAD and HVAD pump transplant in India in 2012 and 2013 respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian boy, 8, embraces \u2018rejected\u2019 heart at Chennai hospital - Times of India \u25ba |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/russian-boy-8-embraces-rejected-heart-at-chennai-hospital/articleshow/63375518.cms |work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\nHe is the member of [[Indian Medical Association]].<ref>{{cite web |